Analyzing Product to gauge Positive and Negative Influencing Factors

By : Saama Technologies (October, 2016)

1: Executive Summary :

In this Analysis, we choose one of the popular DNA Products, with sizable Review Comments. We then extract those reviews through Web Scraping, Build the Local Corpus, Then apply Sentiment Analysis to it and finally derive Top Influencing Positive & Negative Factors impacting it. The Conclusion Section, at the bottom of this report, lists those factors.

2: Selecting the product and Reviews

For this exercise, we selected Cisco RV110W-A-NA-K9 Small Business RV110W Wireless N VPN Firewall Router on Amazon.com

Cisco Router.

Here are some Review Comments about this Router,

Product Reviews.

3: Extracting Reviews

3.1: Web Scraping

Our analysis was entirely done in R. One of the most popular, Statistical languages.

After the Website and the Product was chosen, we wrote R-Code to,

  • Scrape the Website
  • Extract Relevent Review Comments
  • Store them As Local Corpus

3.2: Building the Corpus & Applying Pre-processing

This Corpus needed lot of Pre-Processing.

Some of the Pre-processing applied was :

  • Remove URLs
  • Remove Non-English Letters and Spaces
  • Convert Text to Lower Case
  • Stem Words
  • Remove StopWords
  • Remove Extra Whitespace

6: Conclusion

  1. Strongly Positive Influencing Factors were : excellent router, easy configure, great price, awesome deal, top quality, great range
  2. Positive Influencing Factors were : stable router, excellent wifi, good signal
  3. Negative Influencing Factors were : slow connection, crummy hardware, unknown protocol, disabled client
  4. Strongly Negative Influencing Factors were : difficult set, multiple ssid
  5. This analysis was done on a limited data-set of 166 Review Comments. Detailed Analysis can be performed on Larger Review Data-set
  6. The Sentiment Dictionary was built, based on Positive and Negative words of Equal Weightage. This Weightage can be varied to get better results
